[Task bayes-t548-v2] PHASE 3a: PLAN
Title: Implement bounded-treewidth exact inference module skeleton (rebased)

Read .fleet/tasks/bayes-t548-v2/questions.json and .fleet/tasks/bayes-t548-v2/research.json
for context on what was asked and answered.

YOU MUST create .fleet/tasks/bayes-t548-v2/plan.json with this structure:
{
  "phase": "plan",
  "decisions": [
    { "id": "d1", "decision": "...", "based_on": ["q1"], "alternatives_rejected": ["..."], "reversibility": "easy|medium|hard" }
  ],
  "steps": [
    { "step": 1, "task": "...", "depends_on": [] }
  ],
  "spawn_children": false,
  "children": []
}

DO NOT STOP until plan.json exists and contains at least one step.
Verify: ls -la .fleet/tasks/bayes-t548-v2/ to confirm the file was written.

DECOMPOSITION: Set spawn_children=true for independent sub-tasks that warrant
their own 4-phase workflow. Format: { "id": "...", "title": "...", "description": "..." }

BEFORE YOU STOP: git add -A && git commit --no-verify -m "plan: bayes-t548-v2"

